To determine its structure, compound 1 was purified from AabrBOS1 -transformed yeast cultures by column chromatography and analyzed by NMR spectroscopy. Correlations observed in 2D-NMR spectra ( Figs. S4–S 14 and Supplementary Table S2 ) revealed the structure of this compound to be α- bisabolol. Comparisons with 1 H and 13 C-NMR spectroscopic data of standard (-)-α- bisabolol (Figs. S15 and S16 and Supplementary Table S3) and reported data of (-)- epi -α- bisabolol (
) further confirmed that compound 1 was not epi -α- bisabolol. Specific rotation analysis showed that the [α] D 12 of this compound was +59.5 ( c 0.26, MeOH), which was sufficiently close to the reported value of (+)-α- bisabolol of [α] D 20 +57.04 (MeOH) (
). Thus, compound 1 was identified as (+)-α- bisabolol ( Fig. 4C ), indicating that AabrBOS1–4 are (+)-α- bisabolol synthases.

We previously identified (+)-α- bisabolol synthases from
A . kurramensis
and
A . maritima
